# Managed by bootstrap (fullstack profile). Prettier owns the front-end source
# only — every other part of the repo belongs to another tool: markdownlint →
# Markdown, actionlint → GitHub workflows, PHP-CS-Fixer → PHP, the package
# managers → lockfiles. Letting Prettier loose on all of them makes
# `prettier --check .` (and lint-staged) fight hand-authored config and docs.
#
# So: ignore everything, then re-include just the front-end surface. Front-end
# code is expected under assets/ (same convention as tsconfig.json's `include`);
# adjust the re-includes below if your front lives elsewhere.

# Always-off: generated or vendored output.
node_modules/
vendor/
dist/
build/
public/build/
public/bundles/
var/
*.min.js
*.min.css

# Ignore everything at the repo root by default…
/*

# …then re-include the front-end source and its Prettier-owned config.
!/assets/
!/eslint.config.js
!/tsconfig.json
!/.prettierrc
!/.lintstagedrc.json
